Game Title
Memory Match Challenge
=======================
Game Description
Memory Match Challenge is a simple and fun browser‑based puzzle game built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
The goal is to flip cards, remember their positions, and find all matching pairs.
This project helps beginners strengthen their front‑end development skills while learning how to use GitHub and version control.
The game runs directly in the browser—no installations required—and can be published using GitHub Pages for a live online demo.
========================
How to Play
• Click any card to flip it.
• Flip a second card to try to find a matching pair.
• If the cards match, they remain revealed.
• If they don’t match, they will flip back after a short delay.
• Continue until all pairs are matched.
• Press the “Restart Game” button to play again.
